#10203
Name:	A Hugh Mirror Hangs in the Void
Desc:$
   You materialize, hanging once again in a void. This time, no stars or
constellations mark you position. This is emptiness made real. You feel as
insignificant as a bacilli. Momentarily, the shape of space begins to fold in
on itself and coagulate. A form begins to manifest. Before you is a gigantic
mirror. Like the Dweller before, it seems to fill your view, until you
eventually realize, it does not just exist before you but all around you. You
are encapsulated within a reflective sphere. You peer into it and around it
but only your own countenance stares back at you. You feel an eerie sense of
malevolent intelligent in these images, as though they stare back at you, know
you, plotting your demise, dissecting your very soul! 
~
