#10208
Name:	A Clear Blue Sky
Desc:$
   ^CYou hover within a clear blue sky. Looking, to what you believe would be
down, you see nothing. There is no land upon which to descend and rest. This
is a place of ether, of atmosphere alone. You begin to notice that the sky is
not as empty and clear as you first thought. Lazy clouds of purest white float
within it. Though you note that they seem to move not at random, but almost
with a purpose and a defined destination. Suddenly, a wind whips you, chilling
you to your very soul. ^cThe air becomes rough and seems to almost flay the skin
from your bones. The once welcoming clouds begin to take on a darker shade and
winds howl in your ears. Soon, you are in the midest of a swirling mass of
air, the likes of which, you have never known! You notice shapes, horrifying
shades of destruction, within the dark, lightning shot clouds. ^LYou hang now,
suspended, within the very eye of a huricane. The shapes begins to dart out of
the tight moving circle, turning their attention to you!^N 
~
